   creating your own animated pause prompts
   ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ-Ä-ùú

   the animated pause system works just like the random display file system
   that mystic bbs uses.  animated pause prompt files are stored in the
   text directory under the file name "anipause.tx?" where ? is replaced by
   the randomly selected extention.  using this system, valid filenames
   are:
        anipause.txt
        anipause.tx1
        anipause.tx2
        anipause.tx3
        anipause.tx4
        anipause.tx5
        anipause.tx6
        anipause.tx7
        anipause.tx8
        anipause.tx9

   each pause file is a straight dos text file - editable with your favorite
   text editor.  the first line is the number of milliseconds to pause after
   each line is displayed.  it is recommended that this value is never
   greater than 200.  after the first line, each line after until the end
   of the file will be displayed in order.  when the last line is displayed,
   the pause engine will loop back to the first line.

   (NOTE) each pause file can be no longer than 50 lines long.  if you do
   not understand how the pause files work, look at the examples included.

